{"number":1,"category":"marriage","header":"Daughter's marriage produced a Hooker cousin convergence","body":"Caroline married Rev. George Kemp Ward in 1873 and bore four children — Levi, Ruth, Charles, and Kenneth — all Hooker descendants through her Pierpont line. When her daughter Ruth married Horace Willard Hooker in 1906, the union produced the project's third documented Hooker-Hooker cousin marriage, with both spouses tracing descent to Rev. Thomas Hooker through different branches."}],"slug":"caroline-pierpont-1852"},"X01665":{"id":"X01665","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"tags":["minister","author","academic"],"sources":[{"label":"FindAGrave — Rev George Kemp Ward","url":"https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/26753459/george_kemp-ward"},{"label":"Princeton Magazine, Vol. 6 (1891), pp. 428-9 — biographical sketch","url":"https://books.google.com/books?id=vmE9AQAAMAAJ&pg=PA428"}],"gender":"male","number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"HD1545","date_year":1873,"date_month":5,"date_day":18,"location_state":"New York","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1937,"children_ids":["HD3407","HD3401","HD3400","HD3402","HD3403"]}],"parents":{},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"birth":{"year":1848,"month":1,"day":9,"city":"Rochester","county":"Monroe","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1937,"month":7,"day":18,"city":"Bronxville","county":"Westchester","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Rev. George Kemp Ward","first_name":"George","middle_name":"Kemp","last_name":"Ward","title":"Reverend","married_names":[],"extra_names":"M.A.","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1777607291/gerogekempward_vnathx.jpg","photo_notes":"Portrait. Cloudinary."},"residence":{"city":"Dansville","county":"Livingston","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST023","relationship":"alumnus","years":"1865-1869","institution_blurb":"Class of 1869, A.M. 1872. Class Secretary and Historian; American Whig Society; Iota Chapter of Delta Psi."},{"institution_id":"INST145","relationship":"alumnus"}],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM170","plot_notes":"LittleVille Cemetery, Avon NY. FindAGrave 26753459."},"education":[{"school_name":"Rochester Collegiate Institute","type":"preparatory","notes":"Preliminary training; later attended the University of Rochester in his Freshman year before transferring to Princeton."},{"school_name":"University of Rochester","dates":"ca.1864-1865","type":"undergraduate","notes":"Mid-Freshman year transfer to Princeton."},{"institution_id":"INST023","dates":"1865-1869","type":"undergraduate","notes":"Princeton class of 1869; member of the American Whig Society; Iota Chapter of Delta Psi (joined at Rochester); elected Secretary and Historian of his class."},{"institution_id":"INST023","dates":"1872","type":"graduate","notes":"Master of Arts (A.M.) Princeton University."},{"institution_id":"INST145","school_name":"Princeton Theological Seminary","dates":"1869-1873","type":"seminary","notes":"Prepared for the ministry of the Presbyterian Church."}],"career":[{"role":"Pastor","organization":"Dansville Presbyterian Church","location":"Dansville, New York","start_year":1873,"end_year":1898,"notes":"First and only pastoral charge — twenty-five years. Twice Moderator of the Presbytery of Rochester; editor of the Presbyterian Church Herald; member of the Livingston County Historical Society."},{"role":"Secretary","organization":"Association of Descendants of Andrew Ward","notes":"Compiler of the Andrew Ward Family Genealogy."},{"role":"Author","organization":"self-published / Princeton class historian","notes":"Published two volumes of class history: 'After Nine Years' (1878) and 'The Vigintennial Volume of 1869' (1889) — a finely illustrated twenty-year record of the Princeton class. Also published several religious pamphlets including 'The Strength of Young Manhood' and 'The Memorial of Elizabeth Dippy'."}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"education","header":"Switched colleges mid-freshman year for Princeton","body":"George began his college career at the University of Rochester but, midway through his Freshman year, transferred to Princeton — bringing his Iota Chapter of Delta Psi membership with him. He graduated as Old Nassau's Class Secretary and Historian in 1869, then earned his A.M. in 1872 and finished at Princeton Theological Seminary the next year."},{"number":2,"category":"religion","header":"Twenty-five-year pastorate at Dansville Presbyterian","body":"After ordination George took the pastorate at Dansville Presbyterian Church in upstate New York and stayed for a quarter century — from 1873 until 1898. Twice elected Moderator of the Presbytery of Rochester, he edited the Presbyterian Church Herald and sat on the Livingston County Historical Society alongside his pastoral work."},{"number":3,"category":"literature","header":"Compiled the Andrew Ward Family Genealogy","body":"As Secretary of the Association of Descendants of Andrew Ward, George compiled the family genealogy that traces the Ward line back to East Haddam Connecticut. He also published two Princeton class histories — 'After Nine Years' (1878) and 'The Vigintennial Volume of 1869' (1889) — the latter a finely illustrated twenty-year reunion record."},{"number":4,"category":"family","header":"Father was former Mayor of Rochester New York","body":"George was the son of Hon. Levi A. Ward, a former Mayor of Rochester, and the grandson of Dr. Levi Ward, a pioneer of Western New York who had emigrated from East Haddam Connecticut early in the 19th century. He was also a cousin of Prof. Henry A."},{"number":5,"category":"family","header":"Cousin of the Rochester natural-science magnate","body":"George was a first cousin of Prof. Henry Augustus Ward, the naturalist who founded Ward's Natural Science Establishment in Rochester. The firm supplied geological, zoological, and anthropological specimens to universities and museums across the United States — and the cousins shared the Rochester Ward extended family's scholarly orientation, George turning to ministry and genealogy where Henry turned to natural history."},{"number":6,"category":"family","header":"Grandfather pioneered Western New York from Connecticut","body":"George's grandfather Dr. Levi Ward emigrated from East Haddam Connecticut early in the 19th century and was among the pioneer settlers of Western New York, establishing the Ward family in Rochester. The migration west from a Connecticut town that itself had been a 17th-century Puritan settlement carried the family's New England Calvinist culture into the Genesee Valley."}],"slug":"george-ward-1848"},"HD3407":{"id":"HD3407","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"bio":{"display_name":"Edwards Pierpont Ward","first_name":"Edwards","middle_name":"Pierpont","last_name":"Ward","married_names":[],"photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1777609394/edwardpierpontward-resized_rktw4i.png","photo_notes":"Portrait. Cloudinary."},"birth":{"year":1874,"month":4,"day":30,"city":"New York","county":"New York","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1957,"month":9,"day":29,"city":"Geneseo","county":"Livingston","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"residence":{"city":"New York","county":"New York","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"burial":{},"gender":"male","classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"is_easter_egg":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1},"parents":{"father_id":"X01665","mother_id":"HD1545","father_research_notes":"Father Rev. George Kemp Ward (X01665).","mother_research_notes":"Mother Caroline Editha Pierpont Ward (HD1545). Edwards's middle name 'Pierpont' carries her maiden surname forward — distinctive among his four siblings, none of whom received the Pierpont middle name. See naming_inspiration."},"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"I00344","date_year":1902,"date_month":10,"date_day":21,"location_state":"New York","location_country":"United States","children_ids":["HD3408","HD3409","HD3410","HD3411","HD3412","HD3413"]},{"marriage_number":2,"spouse_id":"I00345","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1957,"children_ids":["HD3414"]}],"number_of_marriages":2,"tags":[],"research_tags":[],"sources":[{"label":"FamilySearch — Edwards Pierpont Ward","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/tree/person/K4LY-S6L"}],"research_sources":[],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Only sibling carrying mother's maiden surname Pierpont","body":"Of George Kemp Ward and Caroline Editha Pierpont's five children, only Edwards — the eldest — received his mother's maiden surname Pierpont as his middle name. His daughter Carolyn Pierpont Ward (b.1914) carried the pattern forward to a third generation, and Carolyn's first name Carolyn itself echoes her grandmother Caroline."}],"cross_connections":[],"naming_inspiration":[{"name_element":"Pierpont","inspired_by_id":"HD1545","description":"Middle name carries his mother's maiden surname Pierpont forward — and through her the broader Pierpont line back to Mary Hooker Pierpont and Thomas Hooker. Of George + Caroline's five children, only Edwards (the eldest) carries this middle name."}],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"documents":[],"quotes":[],"statues":[],"slug":"edwards-ward-1874"},"HD3401":{"id":"HD3401","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"display_name":"Levi Alfred Ward","first_name":"Levi","middle_name":"Alfred","last_name":"Ward","married_names":[]},"birth":{"year":1876,"month":3,"day":11,"city":"Dansville","county":"Livingston","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1944,"city":"Rochester","county":"Monroe","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM153","plot_notes":"Mount Hope Cemetery, Rochester NY. FindAGrave 72197309."},"gender":"male","classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"is_easter_egg":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1},"parents":{"father_id":"X01665","mother_id":"HD1545","father_research_notes":"Father Rev. George Kemp Ward (X01665).","mother_research_notes":"Mother Caroline Editha Pierpont Ward (HD1545); Hooker descent runs through her Pierpont line. Levi carries his paternal grandfather's name (Hon. Levi A. Ward, Mayor of Rochester) — see naming_inspiration."},"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"I00339","date_year":1905,"location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1944,"children_ids":["HD3404"]}],"number_of_marriages":1,"tags":[],"research_tags":[],"sources":[{"label":"FindAGrave — Levi Alfred Ward","url":"https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/72197309/levi_alfred-ward"}],"research_sources":[],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Named for his mayoral Rochester grandfather","body":"Born in Dansville while his father Rev. George Kemp Ward held the Presbyterian pastorate there, Levi carried his paternal grandfather's name forward. Hon. Levi A. Ward had served as Mayor of Rochester earlier in the 19th century — making the eldest son's first and middle names a two-generation civic legacy bound up in the Rochester Ward family."}],"cross_connections":[],"naming_inspiration":[{"name_element":"Levi Alfred","description":"Named for his paternal grandfather Hon. Levi A. Ward, who served as Mayor of Rochester NY in the mid-19th century. Hon. Levi A. Ward is not built into the JSON tree — he is the father of George Kemp Ward (X01665), Caroline Editha Pierpont's husband, and not himself a Hooker descendant."}],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"documents":[],"quotes":[],"statues":[],"slug":"levi-ward-1876"},"HD3400":{"id":"HD3400","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"bio":{"display_name":"Ruth Ward Hooker","first_name":"Ruth","middle_name":"Ward","last_name":"Hooker","maiden_name":"Ward","married_names":["Hooker"]},"birth":{"year":1879,"month":6,"day":30,"city":"Rochester","county":"Monroe","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1967,"month":4,"day":18,"city":"Geneseo","county":"Livingston","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM153","plot_notes":"Mount Hope Cemetery, Rochester NY. FindAGrave 26515170."},"gender":"female","classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"is_easter_egg":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1},"parents":{"father_id":"X01665","mother_id":"HD1545","father_research_notes":"Father Rev. George Kemp Ward (X01